      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm seeing a 500 error on our /api/v1/checkout/complete endpoint. it's intermittent but seems to happen most during peak traffic. here is the snippet from the error logs:\n\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] ERROR: Internal Server Error - Request ID: 7721-ax\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] STACKTRACE: \n  at OrderService.processPayment (OrderService.ts:142:12)\n  at CheckoutController.handleRequest (CheckoutController.ts:45:9)\n  at Middleware.execute (Middleware.ts:12:4)\n  Caused by: ConnectionTimeoutException: Pool exhaustion detected in 'db_pool_main'\n  at DatabaseDriver.getConnection (driver.js:88:2)\n\nany idea what's causing this?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
